sentences: David Barbarossa (born 1961, also known as Dave Barbe) is a drummer and an author of British and Mauritian descent.

As part of both Adam and the Ants and Bow Wow Wow, he was instrumental in creating the highly influential and innovative tribal drumming style that was popular among British and some American bands from 1979 to 1983.
Barbarossa joined Adam and the Ants in 1977 and was the drummer for their debut album Dirk Wears White Sox.
